.TH SHOREWALLD 8 "2026-04-12" "shorewall-nft 1.4.0" "System Administration"
.SH NAME
shorewalld \- Prometheus exporter and DNS-driven nft-set daemon for shorewall-nft
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B shorewalld
.RI [ OPTIONS ]
.PP
.B shorewalld tap
.B \-\-socket
.I PATH
.RI [ OPTIONS ]
.SH DESCRIPTION
.B shorewalld
is the companion daemon for
.BR shorewall-nft (8).
It serves two independent jobs, both off by default:

.TP
.B Prometheus exporter
Scrapes per-rule packet/byte counters, per-interface stats, and
conntrack fill level from every
.I inet shorewall
table on the system, across all network namespaces, via a single
libnftables round-trip per scrape cycle. Exposes them at a
Prometheus text endpoint (default \fB:9748\fR).

.TP
.B DNS-set API
Accepts a dnstap FrameStream (or PBDNSMessage protobuf stream) from
.BR pdns-recursor (8)
and keeps nft sets named \fIdns_<qname>_v4\fR / \fIdns_<qname>_v6\fR
populated with the resolved A/AAAA records. This allows
.B shorewall-nft
rules to match on hostnames rather than literal IP addresses:
.RS
.nf
ACCEPT  fw  net:dns:github.com  tcp  443
.fi
.RE
The compiler declares the sets; shorewalld populates them.

Running
.B shorewalld
with no options starts it in Prometheus-only mode.

.SH OPTIONS
.TP
.BI \-\-listen\-prom " HOST:PORT"
Prometheus scrape endpoint (default: \fB:9748\fR).
.TP
.BI \-\-listen\-api " PATH"
Unix socket for the dnstap FrameStream consumer. Off by default.
Set to e.g. \fB/run/shorewalld/dnstap.sock\fR to enable the DNS-set API.
.TP
.BI \-\-dnstap\-tcp " HOST:PORT"
Accept dnstap FrameStream over TCP in addition to the unix socket.
Used when the recursor is in a different mount namespace or on a
remote host.
.TP
.BI \-\-pbdns\-tcp " HOST:PORT"
Accept PBDNSMessage (pdns_recursor protobuf) over TCP.
pdns_recursor refuses unix sockets for \fBprotobufServer()\fR.
.TP
.BI \-\-netns " SPEC"
Namespace selection. \fB(empty)\fR = daemon's own netns only.
\fBauto\fR = walk \fI/run/netns/\fR. Comma-separated list =
explicit namespaces (e.g. \fBfw,rns1,rns2\fR).
.TP
.BI \-\-scrape\-interval " SECS"
Per-netns ruleset cache TTL in seconds (default: 30).
.TP
.BI \-\-reprobe\-interval " SECS"
How often to re-check which namespaces have a loaded
.I inet shorewall
table (default: 300).
.TP
.BI \-\-log\-level " LEVEL"
Log level: \fBdebug\fR, \fBinfo\fR, \fBwarning\fR, \fBerror\fR.
.TP
.BI \-\-config\-file " PATH"
Path to configuration file (default: \fI/etc/shorewall/shorewalld.conf\fR
then \fI/etc/shorewalld.conf\fR).
.TP
.BI \-\-state\-dir " DIR"
Directory for DNS set state persistence (default: \fI/var/lib/shorewalld\fR).
.TP
.B \-\-state\-flush
Ignore and delete any saved DNS set state on startup.
.TP
.B \-\-no\-state\-load
Ignore saved state but do not delete it.

.SH tap SUBCOMMAND
.B shorewalld tap
is an inspection tool that binds a dnstap unix socket and
pretty-prints every DNS answer frame it receives. Useful for
verifying that
.B pdns-recursor
is sending frames and tuning the DNS allowlist.

.PP
.RS
.nf
shorewalld tap \-\-socket /run/shorewalld/dnstap.sock \e
               \-\-format pretty \e
               \-\-allowlist /etc/shorewall/dnsnames.compiled
.fi
.RE

.TP
.BI \-\-socket " PATH"
Unix socket path to listen on (required).
.TP
.BI \-\-format " FORMAT"
Output format: \fBpretty\fR (default on TTY), \fBstructured\fR
(key=value for grep), \fBjson\fR (for jq).
.TP
.BI \-\-filter\-qname " REGEX"
Show only frames with qnames matching this regex.
.TP
.BI \-\-filter\-rcode " NAME"
Filter by DNS rcode: \fBNOERROR\fR, \fBNXDOMAIN\fR, etc.
.TP
.BI \-\-allowlist " PATH"
Path to \fIdnsnames.compiled\fR — frames are tagged with
\fB[allowlist ✓]\fR or \fB[unknown]\fR.
.TP
.BI \-\-count " N"
Exit after N matching frames (also prints a summary).
.TP
.B \-\-show\-queries
Include CLIENT_QUERY frames (default: responses only).
.TP
.B \-\-no\-color
Force plain output even on a TTY.

.SH CONFIGURATION FILE
Settings in \fBshorewalld.conf\fR (shell key=value, # comments, optional quoting).
CLI flags always override file values. Unknown keys are silently ignored;
malformed values raise an error at startup.
.PP
Example:
.RS
.nf
LISTEN_PROM=:9748
NETNS=fw,rns1,rns2
SCRAPE_INTERVAL=30
REPROBE_INTERVAL=300

LISTEN_API=/run/shorewalld/dnstap.sock
SOCKET_MODE=0660
SOCKET_GROUP=pdns

PEER_LISTEN=0.0.0.0:9749
PEER_ADDRESS=10.0.0.2:9749
PEER_SECRET_FILE=/etc/shorewall/peer.key
PEER_HEARTBEAT_INTERVAL=5

STATE_DIR=/var/lib/shorewalld
LOG_LEVEL=info
LOG_TARGET=syslog
LOG_FORMAT=structured
.fi
.RE

.SH PROMETHEUS METRICS
Scrape endpoint: \fBhttp://HOST:PORT/metrics\fR (plain text).
All metrics carry a \fBnetns\fR label (empty = daemon's own namespace).

.B Rule metrics
(only when inet shorewall table is loaded in that netns):
.RS
.nf
shorewall_nft_packets_total        counter  netns,chain,rule_handle,comment
shorewall_nft_bytes_total          counter  netns,chain,rule_handle,comment
shorewall_nft_named_counter_packets_total  counter  netns,name
shorewall_nft_named_counter_bytes_total   counter  netns,name
shorewall_nft_set_elements         gauge    netns,set
.fi
.RE

.B Interface metrics
(always, one per netns):
.RS
.nf
shorewall_nft_iface_rx_packets_total   counter  netns,iface
shorewall_nft_iface_rx_bytes_total     counter  netns,iface
shorewall_nft_iface_tx_packets_total   counter  netns,iface
shorewall_nft_iface_tx_bytes_total     counter  netns,iface
shorewall_nft_iface_oper_state         gauge    netns,iface  (1=UP, 0=DOWN)
.fi
.RE

.B Conntrack metrics:
.RS
.nf
shorewall_nft_ct_count   gauge  netns
shorewall_nft_ct_max     gauge  netns
.fi
.RE

.B dnstap pipeline metrics
(only when \fB\-\-listen\-api\fR is set):
.RS
.nf
shorewalld_dnstap_frames_accepted_total
shorewalld_dnstap_frames_decode_error_total
shorewalld_dnstap_frames_dropped_queue_full_total
shorewalld_dnstap_connections         gauge
shorewalld_dnstap_workers_busy        gauge
shorewalld_dnstap_queue_depth         gauge
.fi
.RE

.SH FILES
.TP
.I /etc/shorewall/shorewalld.conf
Primary configuration file location.
.TP
.I /etc/shorewalld.conf
Fallback configuration file location.
.TP
.I /etc/shorewall/dnsnames.compiled
Written by \fBshorewall\-nft start\fR. Contains the set of hostnames
registered via \fBdns:\fR rule syntax and any per-host overrides.
shorewalld reads this as its DNS-set allowlist.
.TP
.I /var/lib/shorewalld/
Default state directory. The daemon persists DNS set contents here
so sets survive daemon restarts without waiting for the recursor to
re-answer every name.
.TP
.I /run/shorewalld/
Runtime directory (created by the systemd unit via RuntimeDirectory=).
Unix sockets live here.
.TP
.I packaging/systemd/shorewalld.service
Recommended systemd unit (single process, --netns auto).
.TP
.I packaging/systemd/shorewalld@.service
Templated unit for per-netns process isolation.
.TP
.I packaging/pdns-recursor/shorewalld.lua.template
Lua config template for pdns_recursor to enable the dnstap stream.

.SH EXIT STATUS
.TP
.B 0
Clean shutdown (SIGTERM or SIGINT).
.TP
.B 1
Fatal startup or runtime error.
.TP
.B 2
Argument or configuration error.

.SH EXAMPLES
.PP
Start with Prometheus metrics only (all namespaces):
.RS
.nf
shorewalld \-\-listen\-prom :9748 \-\-netns auto
.fi
.RE
.PP
Enable the DNS-set API alongside metrics:
.RS
.nf
shorewalld \-\-listen\-prom :9748 \e
           \-\-listen\-api /run/shorewalld/dnstap.sock \e
           \-\-netns auto
.fi
.RE
.PP
Inspect the live dnstap stream with allowlist tagging:
.RS
.nf
shorewalld tap \-\-socket /run/shorewalld/dnstap.sock \e
               \-\-allowlist /etc/shorewall/dnsnames.compiled \e
               \-\-count 100
.fi
.RE
.PP
Override the systemd unit without editing it:
.RS
.nf
mkdir \-p /etc/systemd/system/shorewalld.service.d
cat > /etc/systemd/system/shorewalld.service.d/override.conf <<'EOF'
[Service]
ExecStart=
ExecStart=/usr/bin/shorewalld \e
    \-\-listen\-prom 0.0.0.0:9748 \e
    \-\-listen\-api /run/shorewalld/dnstap.sock \e
    \-\-netns auto
EOF
systemctl daemon\-reload && systemctl restart shorewalld
.fi
.RE

